The paper discusses graph spanners, which are a fundamental concept in computer science and graph theory. The paper covers various aspects of graph spanners, including their formulations, sparsity and lightness results, computational complexity, dynamic algorithms, and applications. These topics are all related to different subfields of computer science, such as data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
